SIMPLE: equipotential
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Equipotential
<hw>E`qui*po*ten"tial</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Equi-</ets> + <ets>potential</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Mech. &
Physics)</fld> <def>Having the same potential.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Equipotential surface</b></col>, <cd>a surface for which
the potential is for all points of the surface constant. Level surfaces
on the earth are <xex>equipotential</xex>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Equiradical</ent>⟦br⟧
